OL,3,CPoet-ree trail for Birmingham poet
OL,4,CBenjamin Zephaniah
OL,6,FHis sister, Millicent Springer, said
OL,7,Fthis was a fitting tribute to her
OL,8,Fbrother.
OL,10,F"Benjamin would have absolutely loved
OL,11,Fthis. He'd probably be running around
OL,12,Fthe trees and doing some of his
OL,13,Fpoetry. It's bringing the community
OL,14,Ftogether and people together from all
OL,15,Fwalks of life and different community,
OL,16,Freligions."
